# What Makes Decision Systems Different?

> Draft

---

## Motivation

Not every system that has more than one possible action to adopt appears to have what is necessary to say it has made a decision. 

A thermostat, a bacterium, a reinforcement learning agent and a human all produce actions, yet they differ in their ability to modify how those actions are selected - and if there was a choice to be made.

This note explores whether different classes of decision systems exist.

It does not assume that the answer is yes.

This classification is hypothetical.

## Decision Capabilities

- Perceives the environment

- Represents the environment

- Identifies alternatives

- Selects an alternative

- Executes an action

- Evaluates the outcome

- Updates its decision policy

□ Updates its own representation

□ Generates new alternatives
